flowRoot.flowPara: Shared edges between thumbnails exert an attractive force. This means that, when dragged, thumbnails will move along the axis of their shared edges, unless the pointer is moved in an opposing direction to that axis by a certain distance.
If the thumbnail is pulled away from is shared edges, it becomes unstuck and can be freely dragged. Any other displays automatically rearrange so there aren't gaps between them.
This allows moving a thumbnail along an existing axis, as an operation that is distinct from changing the joined edges or moving the thumbnail entirely.

flowRoot.flowPara: Shared edges don't have "corners" - thumbnails don't slide around oneanother. In the following example, it wouldn't be possible to move the thumbnail to the left, other than to detach it from the joined edge it shares with the other display.
